BATAVIA, N.Y. (AP) _ Graham Corp. (GHM) on Wednesday reported a fiscal fourth-quarter loss of $1.4 million, after reporting a profit in the same period a year earlier.On a per-share basis, the Batavia, New York-based company said it had a loss of 13 cents. Losses, adjusted for non-recurring costs, came to 2 cents per share.The maker of vacuum and heat-transfer equipment posted revenue of $39.7 million in the period.For the year, the company reported a loss of $8.8 million, or 83 cents per share, swinging to a loss in the period. Revenue was reported as $122.8 million.Graham expects full-year revenue in the range of $135 million to $150 million._____This story was generated by Automated Insights (http://automatedinsights.com/ap) using data from Zacks Investment Research. Access a Zacks stock report on GHM at https://www.zacks.com/ap/GHM